  "text": "What was the the only question I was going to ask that I can think of was could you give me the average lifespan of the Atlantic Atlantean population? I am raw. The average lifespan, as we have said, is misleading. The Atlanteans were in the early part of their cultural experience used to life spans from seventy to one hundred forty years, this being, of course, approximate due to increasing desire for power. The lifetime decreased rapidly in the later stages of this civilization, and thus the healing and rejuvenating information was requested. Do you have any brief queries before we close?",
